African Americans are one of the largest ethnic groups in the United States. 
Data from the U.S. Department of Commerce, Bureau of the Census (2001) reveal 
that there are approximately 34,333,000 African Americans residing in the United 
States, representing 12.1% of the total population. The African-American 
